cc <- clusters(g)

d) Calculate the average polarity of the tweets of the users in the graph and study the correlation between that average and their influence

#Calculating average polarity for each user

user_avg_polarity <- function(users)
{
  polarity.avg <- vector()
  for (user in users){
    text <- tweets$text[tolower(tweets$screen_name) == user]

    text <- iconv(text,"UTF-8","latin1",sub="") #get rid of emojis, end-of-line characters
    text <- gsub("(RT|via)((?:\\b\\W*@\\w+)+)", "", text) #get rid of retweets
    text = gsub("@\\w+", "", text) #get rid of mentions
    text = gsub("[[:punct:]]", "", text) #get rid of punctuation
    text = gsub("[[:digit:]]", "", text) #get rid of numbers
    text = gsub("http\\w+", "", text) #get rid of html links
    text = gsub("[ \t]{2,}", "", text) #get rid of unnecessary spaces
    text = gsub("^\\s+|\\s+$", "", text)

    polarity.all <- get_sentiment(text, method="bing")
    polarity.avg <- c(polarity.avg, sum(polarity.all)/length(text))
  }
  df <- data.frame(user=users, polarity.avg)
  return(df)
}

Influence and polarity
